description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Recovery College Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Ambrose House, Gloucester&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary –£31,365 to £37,890 per annum, pro rata (Band 6)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 22.5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post presents an exciting opportunity to lead the Severn and Wye Recovery College, part of Gloucestershire Health and Care NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recovery College is an education-based approach empowering people to own and manage their journey to recovery from mental illness. The service offers a range of face to face courses and has recently created an online program in response to covid 19.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an individual who is passionate about co-production and personalised approaches to care to come and work with us to lead and further develop our approach to peer led self-management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are keen to encourage applications from people with lived experience of mental illness who are keen to use their experience to support the recovery of others and/or those with a health professional registration or other relevant qualification and experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion and any enquires please contact Jackie Baker on 01452 894204 or email jackie.baker@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualifications, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
